Police in Kwara State have arrested one Suleiman Tajudeen for allegedly killing a commercial driver on Tuesday in Eiyenkorin area of the state capital. Tajudeen allegedly shot and killed the driver Hammed Idowu for refusing to pay N5,000 bribe. Police spokesman Ajayi Okasanmi confirmed the incident, saying, “A comercial bus reportedly driven by one Hammed Idowu, now late, coming to Ilorin through a bush path in order to avoid the police checkpoint at Eiyenkorin was contravened inside the bush path by a local hunter named Suleiman Tajudeen employed by the Alagbado community, Eyenkorin.” He said Tajudeen shot and killed the driver in an altercation, adding that the development was being investigated.